# Experiencing Music Emotions Through Movement

Code and data for our *neuroscience and musicology* project:

**"Evaluating the motor cortex’s role in generating emotion by comparing cortical inhibition using Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (TMS) to a sham control session"**

**Authors:**
Sofia Knopf (University of British Columbia Okanagan)
Sarah Kraeutner (University of British Columbia Okanagan)
Anja Cui (University of Vienna)

---

## Project Description

This project investigates whether the primary motor cortex (M1) plays a causal role in emotional responses to music. Using continuous theta-burst stimulation (cTBS), participants completed both active and sham sessions. Emotional responses were measured using valence and arousal ratings.

**Research Question:**
Does inhibiting M1 alter perceived emotional responses to music?

